  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Greek rhetor of the 1st cent. BC, probably from Athens. He was the
    younger Cicero's teacher in 44 until the latter's father forbade their contact (Cic. Fam. 16,21,6
    Plut. Cicero 873ab). Seneca (Controv. 1,4,7) mentions G., but the Greek quotations have been lost
    in the transmission. G. wrote a work on figures of speech (περὶ σχημάτων perì schēmátōn) in 4 bks.,
    translated into Latin by his contemporary Rutilius Lupus..." Weißenberger, Michael (Greifswald).
    "Gorgias." Brill’s New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and , Helmuth Schneider. Brill Online, 2015.</mads:note>
